RA q_hat=0.6899 | REINFORCE q_hat=0.7068 | HRA tighter by 2.4%\n  vqa_v2       HRA q_hat=0.9303 | REINFORCE q_hat=0.9210 | REINFORCE tighter\n\n  HRA more EFFICIENT (tighter q_hat, same coverage) on 1/2 benchmarks.\n  >>> Mixed on efficiency too - may need full run or a different nonconformity score.\n\nSaved efficiency_diagnostic.json\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":23},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# CELL 13 — Split Conformal Prediction (core UQ contribution)\n# Tests whether each agent's behaviour supports valid coverage guarantees.\n# Nonconformity score s = 1 - FGM (low FGM = high nonconformity = likely wrong).\n# Calibrate threshold q_hat on calibration split, test coverage on held-out split.\nimport numpy as np\n\nALPHA=CFG[\"CONFORMAL_ALPHA\"]  # 0.1 -> target 90% coverage\ndef split_conformal(scores, alpha=0.1, cal_frac=0.5, seed=0):\n    s=np.array([1.0-x for x in scores])  # nonconformity\n    n=len(s)\n    if n<10: return None\n    rng=np.random.default_rng(seed); idx=rng.permutation(n)\n    n_cal=int(n*cal_frac)\n    cal,test=s[idx[:n_cal]],s[idx[n_cal:]]\n    # conformal quantile\n    q_level=np.ceil((n_cal+1)*(1-alpha))/n_cal\n    q_level=min(q_level,1.0)\n    q_hat=np.quantile(cal,q_level,method=\"higher\")\n    # coverage on test: fraction with nonconformity <= q_hat (i.e., prediction set contains truth)\n    coverage=float(np.mean(test<=q_hat))\n    avg_set_size=float(np.mean(s<=q_hat))  # proxy for set size / efficiency\n    return {\"q_hat\":round(q_hat,4),\"coverage\":round(coverage,4),\n            \"target\":round(1-alpha,4),\"gap\":round(coverage-(1-alpha),4),\n            \"avg_set_size\":round(avg_set_size,4),\"n\":n}\n\nprint(f\"Conformal prediction (target coverage = {1-ALPHA:.0%})\\n\")\nconformal_results={}\nfor bm in [\"scienceqa\",\"vqa_v2\",\"mmbench\",\"textvqa\"]:\n    if bm not in conformal_scores: continue\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*64}\\n{bm.upper()}\\n{'='*64}\")\n    print(f\"  {'Agent':<12}{'Coverage':>10}{'Target':>9}{'Gap':>9}{'SetSize':>9}\")\n    conformal_results[bm]={}\n    for agent in [\"vanilla\",\"reinforce\",\"ppo_clip\",\"hra\"]:\n        seed_scores=conformal_scores[bm].get(agent,{})\n        if not seed_scores: continue\n        # Pool coverage across seeds (each seed = one conformal run)\n        covs,gaps,sizes=[],[],[]\n        for sd,sc in seed_scores.items():\n            res=split_conformal(sc,alpha=ALPHA,seed=sd)\n            if res: covs.append(res[\"coverage\"]); gaps.append(res[\"gap\"]); sizes.append(res[\"avg_set_size\"])\n        if not covs: continue\n        mc,mg,ms=np.mean(covs),np.mean(gaps),np.mean(sizes)\n        conformal_results[bm][agent]={\"coverage_mean\":round(mc,4),\"coverage_std\":round(np.std(covs,ddof=1) if len(covs)>1 else 0,4),\n                                       \"gap_mean\":round(mg,4),\"set_size_mean\":round(ms,4),\"n_seeds\":len(covs)}\n        flag=\"OK\" if abs(mg)<0.05 else \"MISCALIBRATED\"\n        print(f\"  {agent:<12}{mc:>10.4f}{1-ALPHA:>9.2f}{mg:>+9.4f}{ms:>9.4f}  {flag}\")\n\nimport json as _json, os\nwith open(os.path.join(WORK_DIR,\"conformal_results.json\"),\"w\") as f:\n    _json.dump(conformal_results,f,indent=2)\nprint(\"\\nSaved conformal_results.json\")\nprint(\"\\nKEY INSIGHT: An agent is UQ-compatible if coverage approx target with low cross-seed variance.\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-19T15:19:48.108124Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-19T15:19:48.108409Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-19T15:19:48.134413Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-19T15:19:48.108377Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-19T15:19:48.133707Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Conformal prediction (target coverage = 90%)\n\n\n================================================================\nSCIENCEQA\n================================================================\n  Agent         Coverage   Target      Gap  SetSize\n  vanilla         0.9175     0.90  +0.0175   0.9287  OK\n  reinforc